      <p>Stress doesn't follow business hours. It hits when you're trying to fall asleep, during your commute, in the middle of a Sunday afternoon. And when it does, your support options are limited:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Therapy has waitlists and appointments</li>
        <li>Friends have their own lives (and you don't want to be a burden)</li>
        <li>Meditation apps can help, but sometimes you need to <em>talk</em></li>
      </ul>
      <p>You end up spiraling alone, replaying the same thoughts until exhaustion takes over.</p>
